This paper deals with stream processing engines and logical, rule-based reasoning capabilities, which are topics that are commonly studied in the fields of databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes novel reasoning problems and studies their computational properties, which are topics that fall under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of stream reasoning algorithms, which can be related to the field of cryptography (cs.CR) in terms of ensuring the security and privacy of streamed data. Finally, the paper uses Datalog as a core rule-based language, which is a topic that falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL).
